Part I - (Communicate Data findings)¶

by (Oluwafemi OLUWASINA)¶

Introduction¶

The dataset includes information about individual rides made in a bike- sharing system covering different locations stated below.

The datasets I chose for this project are 5 in number which includes:

The ford Go Bike System Data from San Francisco Bay Area,

The Divvy Trips from Chicago, Illinois

The Citibike Trip data from New York City

The Capital Bike Share trip data from washington Dc Metro Area.

The Cogo trip data from Columbus,Ohio.

# to add a column, distance from the coordinates given using pyproj library
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from pyproj import Geod
#Distance will be measured on this ellipsoid - more accurate than a spherical method
wgs84_geod = Geod(ellps='WGS84') 

#Get distance between pairs of lat-lon points
def Distance(lat1,lon1,lat2,lon2):
    az12,az21,dist = wgs84_geod.inv(lon1,lat1,lon2,lat2) #Yes, this order is correct
    return dist

#Create data
lat1 = df_clean['start_station_latitude']
lon1 = df_clean['start_station_longitude']
lat2 = df_clean['end_station_latitude']
lon2 = df_clean['end_station_longitude']

#Add/update a column to the data frame with the distances (in metres)
df_clean['distance'] = Distance(df_clean['start_station_latitude'].tolist(),df_clean['start_station_longitude'].tolist(),df_clean['end_station_latitude'].tolist(),df_clean['end_station_longitude'].tolist())

#lets have a function for replacing repititive coding
def graph (df, xvar, color=sns.color_palette()[0],order=None):
    #dimension of the figure
    plt.figure(figsize=[12,5])
    #graph plot
    k=sns.countplot(data=df, y=xvar, edgecolor='black', color=color, order=order);
    #the total number of variable
    may=df.dropna(subset=[xvar]).shape[0]
    #replace _ with a space
    xvar=xvar.replace('_',' ')
    #graph title
    plt.title(f'''distribution of {xvar}'''.title(), fontsize=14, weight='bold')
    #axis labels
    plt.xlabel(xvar.title(), fontsize=10, weight='bold')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency'.title(), fontsize=10, weight='bold')
    #loop for figure notation
    for p in k.patches:
        k.annotate(f'{((p.get_width()*100)/may):.2f}%',
                   (p.get_width(),p.get_y()+p.get_height()/2),
                   fontsize=12, weight='bold',
                   va='center', ha='left')
    sns.despine()
